OL,6,F"Many people come to us when the money
OL,7,Fthey've received in benefits has run
OL,8,Fout. People have already exhausted all
OL,9,Fother options when they get here -
OL,10,Fthere is no safety net that will catch
OL,11,Fthem anymore.
OL,13,F"Food banks have become an alternative
OL,14,Fto the welfare state, instead of
OL,15,Fcharity that helps the most vulnerable
OL,16,Fin our society through temporary tough
OL,17,Ftimes, this can't continue.
